The article discusses the issue of drug addiction and overdose in America. It emphasizes that the best way to prevent these problems is to prevent people from abusing drugs in the first place. The article mentions that drug abuse has led to the deaths of hundreds of thousands of Americans and highlights the increasing number of babies born drug-dependent and children placed in foster care due to parental drug abuse. President Donald J. Trump has declared a Nationwide Public Health Emergency to address the opioids crisis and has established the President's Commission on Combating Drug Addiction and the Opioid Crisis to lead the fight against drug addiction.